# EXStreamTV Safety Rules

Derived from a full codebase audit (2026-03-20). 30 confirmed bugs across 18 files.
Full reference: docs/LESSONS_LEARNED.md
Short companion: .cursor/rules/exstreamtv-critical.mdc

---

## RULE 01 — Datetime: Always Timezone-Aware (LL-002, LL-015, LL-020)

NEVER use datetime.utcnow() or datetime.now() without tz=timezone.utc.

WRONG:
    now = datetime.utcnow()

CORRECT:
    from datetime import datetime, timezone
    now = datetime.now(tz=timezone.utc)

SQLite returns naive datetimes (no PARSE_DECLTYPES configured in this project).
Always normalise before arithmetic:

    def _ensure_utc(dt):
        if dt is None: return None
        return dt if dt.tzinfo else dt.replace(tzinfo=timezone.utc)

    elapsed = (datetime.now(tz=timezone.utc) - _ensure_utc(db_value)).total_seconds()

---

## RULE 02 — FFmpeg Flags: Always From constants.py (LL-004, LL-005, LL-011, LL-017)

NEVER hardcode FFmpeg flag strings. Always import from exstreamtv/ffmpeg/constants.py.

WRONG:
    cmd.extend(["-fflags", "+genpts+discardcorrupt+fastseek"])
    cmd.extend(["-flags", "+low_delay"])
    cmd.extend(["-af", "loudnorm=I=-24:TP=-2:LRA=7"])

CORRECT:
    from exstreamtv.ffmpeg.constants import FFLAGS_STREAMING, LOUDNORM_FILTER
    cmd.extend(["-fflags", FFLAGS_STREAMING])
    cmd.extend(["-af", LOUDNORM_FILTER])

BANNED flags — never use these:
- -flags +low_delay  (drops B-frames on pre-recorded content, causes A/V desync)
- +fastseek in -fflags  (wrong context for pipe output, masks missing +igndts)
- loudnorm=I=-24  (wrong loudness target, causes volume jumps between items)

