## RULE 04 — Hardware Accel: hwdownload Before format= (LL-012, LL-029)

When hardware decoding is active AND a CPU-side filter is needed, prepend hwdownload.

WRONG (crashes with "Impossible to convert between the formats"):
    filters = ["scale=1920:1080", "format=yuv420p"]

CORRECT:
    is_hw = caps.preferred_method not in (HardwareAccelType.NONE, None)
    if is_hw:
        filters.insert(0, "hwdownload")
    filters.append("format=yuv420p")

---

## RULE 05 — Scheduler Loops: Always Guard Empty Output (LL-001)

Every while loop advancing a time cursor MUST have an else branch that advances the
index if no items are produced. Without this, an empty collection causes 100% CPU spin.

WRONG:
    while current_time < end:
        items = get_items(...)
        if items:
            current_time = items[-1].finish
        # NO ELSE — infinite loop

CORRECT:
    _start_idx = schedule_index
    while current_time < end:
        items = get_items(...)
        if items:
            current_time = items[-1].finish
        else:
            schedule_index = (schedule_index + 1) % len(self.schedule_items)
            if schedule_index == _start_idx:
                break   # full wrap with no output — abort
            continue
        schedule_index = (schedule_index + 1) % len(self.schedule_items)

