## RULE 06 — Database: Never Block the Event Loop (LL-003, LL-013)

NEVER call synchronous SQLAlchemy .execute() or .commit() inside async def.

WRONG:
    async def save_something(self):
        db = self.db_session_factory()
        result = db.execute(stmt)   # BLOCKS ENTIRE EVENT LOOP

CORRECT:
    async def save_something(self):
        loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()
        await loop.run_in_executor(None, self._save_something_sync)

    def _save_something_sync(self):
        db = self.db_session_factory()
        try:
            result = db.execute(stmt)
            db.commit()
        finally:
            db.close()  # ALWAYS in finally

Always pair every db = factory() with finally: db.close().

