## RULE 07 — XMLTV Timestamps: Exactly One Format (LL-007)

ALL programme start/stop attributes MUST use: %Y%m%d%H%M%S +0000

WRONG:
    dt.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S UTC")   # invalid XMLTV
    dt.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ")       # ISO 8601, not XMLTV

CORRECT:
    dt.strftime("%Y%m%d%H%M%S +0000")

Plex silently rejects any programme element with a non-conforming timestamp.

---

## RULE 08 — EPG: Guard None Before strftime (LL-008)

Any variable used in .strftime() MUST be checked for None first.

WRONG:
    start_str = start_time.strftime(...)    # AttributeError if None

CORRECT:
    if start_time is None:
        logger.warning(f"start_time None for channel {ch}, using now")
        start_time = datetime.now(tz=timezone.utc)
    if end_time is None or end_time <= start_time:
        end_time = start_time + timedelta(seconds=1800)
    start_str = start_time.strftime("%Y%m%d%H%M%S +0000")

---

## RULE 09 — Loop Variables: Never Shadow Outer Counters (LL-009)

Inner loops MUST use distinct variable names from outer counters.

WRONG:
    for idx in range(current_item_index):    # shadows outer idx
        item = schedule_items[idx]

CORRECT:
    for _ci in range(current_item_index):
        item = schedule_items[_ci]

---

## RULE 10 — Channel Number: Always Cast to int (LL-010)

FastAPI path parameters are str. Channel.number is int. Always cast explicitly.

WRONG:
    stmt = select(Channel).where(Channel.number == channel_number)

CORRECT:
    try:
        ch = int(channel_number)
    except (ValueError, TypeError):
        raise HTTPException(400, detail=f"Invalid channel number: {channel_number!r}")
    stmt = select(Channel).where(Channel.number == ch)

---

## RULE 11 — Async Locks: Never Await Blocking I/O Inside (LL-013)

async with self._lock must contain only fast non-blocking operations.

WRONG:
    async with self._lock:
        for item in self._items:
            await self._kill_process(item)  # 5s inside lock = deadlock

CORRECT:
    to_kill = []
    async with self._lock:
        for item in list(self._items):
            if item.needs_kill:
                to_kill.append(item)
                del self._items[item.id]
    for item in to_kill:      # outside the lock
        await self._kill_process(item)

---

## RULE 12 — MPEG-TS Buffer: Align Trim to Sync Byte (LL-014)

Any operation slicing an MPEG-TS buffer MUST align to the nearest 0x47 sync byte.

WRONG:
    trimmed = buffer[-max_size:]

CORRECT:
    trimmed = buffer[-max_size:]
    pos = trimmed.find(0x47)
    if pos > 0:
        trimmed = trimmed[pos:]
    elif pos == -1:
        logger.error("No MPEG-TS sync byte — discarding buffer")
        trimmed = b""

---

## RULE 13 — Muxrate: Always Explicit int() Cast (LL-016)

WRONG:
    f"{profile.video_bitrate + profile.audio_bitrate}k"   # silent str concat

CORRECT:
    f"{int(profile.video_bitrate) + int(profile.audio_bitrate)}k"

